Aim :- To configure a GPIO pin as output and blink an LED using softwrae delay.
Apparatus :- STM32f446RE board ; USB Cable ; STM32CubeIDE ; STM32CubeMX
Theory :- STM32 microcontroller has GPIO pjns which can be used as input or output . In this experiment,PA5 is used as output to control the onboard 
    LED(LD2).
    When the pin is set HIGH, LED turns ON, and when LOW , LED turns OFF. By continuously toggling the pin using a delay.\, the LED blinks.
    HAL functions like HAL_GPIO_TogglePin() and HAL_Delay() are used to control the LED easily.
Proceure :-  
   1. Open STM32CubeMX and select STM32F446RE
   2. Configure PA5 as GPIO Output.
   3. Set clock settings
   4. Generate code and open in STM32CubeIDE
   5. Open main.c 
   6. Write code inside while loop
   7. Build the project
   8. Connect board and run program
   9. Observe LED blinking
Observation :-
  * LED blinks continuously
  * Smaller delay gives faster blinking 
  * Larger delay gives slower blinking
Result :- LED successfully blinked using GPIO output and software delay.
Conclusion :- This experiment helped in understanding GPIO output and basic LED control using STM32. It also showed now delay affects blinking speed. 
